<TITLE> Bangladesh win Danone Nations Cup's best fair play trophy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh have won the best fair play trophy in the Danone Nations Cup Under-12 football tournament which concluded Monday in Lyon, France. Bangladesh, represented by the kids of Chittagong, finished 23rd out of 40 teams after playing a total of eight matches in which they beat Italy, Bulgaria, Portugal and Uruguay and lost to Reunion Iceland, Morocco, Vanuatu and England. South Africa emerged champions and hosts France became runners-up. The Bangladeshi kids are scheduled to return home Tuesday afternoon by a Qatar Airways flight. 
